rComments: Excellent prof! Si vous allez en classe et vous prenez des bonnes notes, tout va bien aller. Ne pensez pas que la classe État-Providence est facile- il faut lire toutes les textes et la participation en classe est clé. Les examens sont composées de questions à développement et si vous étudiez, les examens sont simples.

Même si la matière du cours était très théorique, le prof l'expliquait bien. Il fait des retours détaillés sur les lectures et donnait des indices sur les questions d'examens. Il fait certain que tout le monde comprend et donne du temps pour poser des questions. Mais c'est important de prendre des notes, puisque les examens ne sont pas faciles!
C'est un excellent professeur! Sa matière est très intéressante et enrichissante! Il faut juste bien prendre des notes et ne pas rater ses classes!

The prof was very nice and accessible outside class. The readings were mandatory but went over all of them in class, so I didn't read them but ended with a good grade. The mid-term was all short essay (answer 10 out of 15). The exam was not cumulative and short questions + one long answer question that he gives in advance (answer 11 out of 16).

Prof Savard est un exellent prof! Il explique ces termes très bien en classe mais il faut prendre des bonnes notes! Il est très accessible or classe pour répondre tout questions. L'examen mi-session exige que tu étudies toute la matière pour retenir toute, mais les questions sont très juste. Le papier était long mais aussi facile! Bon prof!!
un des meilleur prof  bravo  c'est vraie  ces examens ne sont pas faciles. Mais si vous venez dans ces cours  vous allez être correct. le cours dÉtat providence était très intéressant.
Le professeur essait de garder ses lectures intéressantes avec ses blagues... J'ai trouvé l'examen de mi-session dificile.

Surprisingly a lot of memorization and attention to small detail considering it's a social work course. Go to class because he doesn't post his full slides (and that's the part that counts!) If you are willing to take good notes and write a ridiculously huge paper, it's a guaranteed A.

for some reason, i had an easy time in this class. you need to take good notes, since he almost never puts the full powerpoint on blackboard. he talks about the readings in class so i never did them, and i got an 88 on the midterm (its all about the notes)! theres a midterm, a 12 pg paper and an exam. really boring tho, couldnt say I recommend it!
Sébastien est un  bon professeur, le cours n'est pas très exigeant. Il suffit de faire les lectures et prendre beaucoup de notes en classe et tu auras un A+.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: J'ai pris ce cours il y a longtemps, c'était intéressant mais quand même assez difficile

While he is witty and sarcastic, there is a ridiculous amount of information to take in; a blend of history, economics and politics that you will get bombarded with from day 1. Exams were extremely difficult, failed the first one with a 48 despite hours of studying. Good luck to you.

Witty sense of humour and extremely helpful to his students. However the exams are ridiculously difficult and the information given is almost overwhelming, I know of 8 people (myself included) that failed his first exam (and I studied for days). Very dry subject matter but he does his best to keep it interesting. Expect hours of unending lectures.
Great prof. He is very clear during his lectures and gives good examples. He is always willing to answer your questions and take the time to help you for projects and the exams. Very nice guy.
The teacher was very helpfull and extremely clear with what he expected for the class.
Boring subject being taught by an even more boring prof. Really tough on the grading.
